<item>
            <title>[SPARK-729] Closures not always serialized at capture time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-729</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As seen in &lt;a href=&quot;https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups=#!topic/spark-users/8pTchwuP2Kk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups=#!topic/spark-users/8pTchwuP2Kk&lt;/a&gt; and its corresponding fix on &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mesos/spark/commit/adba773fab6294b5764d101d248815a7d3cb3558&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mesos/spark/commit/adba773fab6294b5764d101d248815a7d3cb3558&lt;/a&gt;, it is possible for a closure referencing a var to see the latest version of that var, instead of the version that was there when the closure was passed to Spark. This is not good when failures or recomputations happen. We need to serialize the closures on capture if possible, perhaps as part of ClosureCleaner.clean.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12705418">SPARK-729</key>
            <summary>Closures not always serialized at capture time</summary>
